                            <comment id="15999309" author="davispw" created="Sat, 6 May 2017 05:57:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just confirming that per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3197?focusedCommentId=15130761&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15130761&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this comment on KAFKA-3197&lt;/a&gt;, this change does not break any ordering guarantees?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15999314" author="enothereska" created="Sat, 6 May 2017 06:18:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davispw&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davispw&quot;&gt;davispw&lt;/a&gt; Yes, setting that variable to 1 attempts to provide ordering guarantees. However the best guarantees (as also discussed on that JIRA) are coming up in 0.11 when exactly-once is enabled. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
